videos.headline: Gerald Coetzee to J Richardson, out Caught by Rohit!! It's a cue-ender and it's gone to Rohit at point. Short into the wicket, Richardson slogs and toe-ends it for an easy catch. The Mumbai Indians are finally smiling and off the blocks. J Richardson c Rohit b Gerald Coetzee 2(2)

Gerald Coetzee to Kushagra, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! Sliced high and Gerald Coetzee has a third. Full delivery in the slot, Kushagra tries to hit the lofted drive straight and slices it high for Tilak to complete a good catch at point. Gerald Coetzee on a hat-trick! Kushagra c Tilak Varma b Gerald Coetzee 0(1)

Gerald Coetzee to Lalit Yadav, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! That is a top catch by Ishan Kishan. Short delivery from Gerald Coetzee, Lalit Yadav looks to pull, gets a thick top edge. Ishan had to run all the way towards short fine leg and dive to complete that catch. Lalit Yadav c Ishan Kishan b Gerald Coetzee 3(4)

Shepherd to Axar, out Axar Run Out!! 1 run completed. Oh Axar! He wasn't aware of the threat at his end. Looked like an easy two with the ball going wide of long-on. Was a slower delivery that was dragged. Axar thought the ball was going to the bowler's end and how well did Ishan Kishan disguise Axar there. Didn't give away that the ball was coming towards him and last second rushed his hands to collect and ignite the stumps. Axar run out (Nabi/Ishan Kishan) 8(7) [4s-1]

Gerald Coetzee to Pant, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! And he throws it away too. Some of the ugliest three shots he's played in his career. If he didn't move his feet to hit attempted yorkers before, now almost yorks himself by moving and when he's in no position still tries to scoop or manufacture a shot. Only ends up slicing it high to the right of Hardik at extra-cover and that should be the game for MI because Stubbs can't do this alone. Pant c Hardik Pandya b Gerald Coetzee 1(3)

Bumrah to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Tim David!! Full toss and it's got him a wicket. Tried the yorker and missed by a big margin. Good thing was he cramped the batter for room so Abishek lost shape on the slog, sliced it high towards long-on and Tim David ain't dropping those. Just six and a wicket in that over Abishek Porel c Tim David b Bumrah 41(31) [4s-5]

Bumrah to Prithvi Shaw, out Bowled!! There's the cunning toe-crusher that forces the batter into hiding his back leg. Bumrah the man for the breakthrough again. Brilliant yorker angling in, Prithvi Shaw was already smart enought to stay leg-side to avoid injury, but this was heading right to that back foot and he had to move it out. Couldn't get his bat down in time and the leg stump lies flat on the ground. End of a decent innings from Shaw. Prithvi Shaw b Bumrah 66(40) [4s-8 6s-3]

Shepherd to Warner, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! Shepherd comes back with a wicket. Wide slower ball full outside off, Warner sinks low to loft, off the toe-end and a dolly to mid-on. That is such a big wicket. Shepherd after the heroics with the bat, now has a wicket. Warner c Hardik Pandya b Shepherd 10(8) [4s-1 6s-1]

Nortje to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by (sub)Fraser-McGurk!! Another underwhelming strike-rate for Hardik Pandya and he goes. A low full-toss on the pads, should have been sent into the stands, instead he finds deep backward square leg and the sub Fraser-McGurk makes no mistake with the reverse-cup. Hardik Pandya c (sub)Fraser-McGurk b Nortje 39(33) [4s-3 6s-1]

Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Axar!! Caught at backward point - short and wide of off, and Tilak couldn't resist the cut - went with hard hands and doesn't bother to keep it down. It's straight down Axar's throat and he ain't dropping any catches this afternoon. MI are scoring at a fast rate, but they're also losing wickets in the process. Tilak Varma c Axar b Khaleel Ahmed 6(5) [4s-1]

Axar to Ishan Kishan, out Caught&Bowled!! That's a screamer and Axar has somehow caught it - dragged shortt and just outside off. Kishan rocked back and then thumped the pull, hard and flat, to the bowler's left - Axar nonchalantly plucked his left hand out and then holds on. He's chuffed to bits, Kishan looks in absolute disbelief, but he'll have to go. A big wicket, Kishan had just started to change gears. Ishan Kishan c and b Axar 42(23) [4s-4 6s-2]

Nortje to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by (sub)Fraser-McGurk!! Wankhede has been silenced, a two-ball duck for Suryakumar Yadav and MI have lost two wickets on the bounce. Pitched up by Nortje and Suryakumar was shaping for the lofted drive - but his weight was on the back-foot and he inside halved the drive, popped in the air and Fraser-McGurk does well to back pedal and complete a two-handed overhead catch. Suryakumar Yadav c (sub)Fraser-McGurk b Nortje 0(2)

Axar to Rohit, out Bowled!! Rohit falls one short of his fifty, but this is a badly needed wicket for DC. Axar kept it flatter and quicker as Rohit came down the pitch, the ball skids through and Rohit is undone by the length, plays all around and loses his off-stump. Thew key was the angle - Axar dragged the length back after that first-ball boundary, kept Rohit guessing and finally gets rid of him. They've taken the strategic break as well. Rohit b Axar 49(27) [4s-6 6s-3]
